Introduction

This is an RNASeq differential expression analysis from paired-end 50 data from Illumina HiSeq 2500 high-output sequencing runs, Combo_HSQ_24 and Combo_HSQ_10 that took place at the NYU Genome Technology Center on November 18, 2014 and August 27, 2014, respectively. The experiment consisted of RNA extracted from mutant mouse cells (TH-A-Mutant, TH-B-Mutant, TH-C-Mutant) compared to control (TH-A-Control, TH-B-Control, TH-C-Control).

The BaseSpace link with run quality information is here: https://basespace.illumina.com/s/nblJAnaXNEuX

1. Data analysis procedure

For CPM data, the alignment program, Bowtie (version 1.0.0) was used with reads mapped to the Ensemble NCBIM37/mm9 (iGenome version) with two mismatches allowed. The uniquely-mapped reads were subjected to subsequent necessary processing, including removal of PCR duplicates, before transcripts were counted with htseq-count. Counts files were imported into the R statistical programming environment and analyzed with the DESeq2 R/Bioconductor package (Love et al. 2014).

Here, data analysis is presented from the thoarcic-level and brachial-level controls. Data analysis for the thoracic-level mutants vs. control can be accessed here:

http://ljcohen.github.io/analyses/Dasen/thoracic/Dasen_RNAseq_report_thoracic.html

and for the brachial-level mutants vs. controls here:

http://ljcohen.github.io/analyses/Dasen/brachial/Dasen_RNAseq_report_brachial.html
